headline: Is the worst over for storage REITs? RBC sees pricing turning positive
summary: Investing.com -- Storage landlords are showing early signs of stabilisation after years of pricing pressure, with RBC Capital Markets arguing that “most things are in place for a storage recovery.”

headline: Brookfield, GIC Agree $4.5 Billion Deal for Australia’s National Storage
summary: The consortium entered into a takeover agreement for the largest self-storage provider in Australia and New Zealand after almost two weeks of exclusive due diligence.
